												<DIV>This was recently discussed on another Necro class board and it was pointed out that people would be zoning around with 2 pets, wich I can see as unbalancing. However, I suggested that only 1 pet should be allowed to zone using the following rules: 1. If there are 2 pets (1&nbsp;"active" and 1 suspended) then the "active" pet will take precedence and zone and the suspended pet would poof. 2. If there is only 1 pet, it should zone whether its "active" OR suspended. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I don't see this as overpowering since pets (FINALLY) now zone. It simply eliminates the need to stop before zoning, unsuspend, zone, resuspend.</DIV>
																		
