			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>I remember reading someplace that the dev team did not like the idea of us running around with two fully buffed pets.&nbsp; I can not help but kind of feel this diminishes the value of Supsend Minion thou.&nbsp; Lets say I get Jober all buffed up and ready for battle in PoK (the one stop buff shopping center) and then make my way to someplace to do a little soloing.&nbsp; Once there I decide having a backup Jober maybe a good idea but here is the problem.&nbsp; I would have to suspend the fully buffed pet to create a second one.&nbsp; Thus really negating the whole point of buffing him in the first place...</P>
<P>Some changes to suspend minion need to be made.&nbsp; It would be nice if we could "hot swap" the pets out.&nbsp; For example lets say I already have a pet up and one suspended, when I use suspend it should mearly swap the suspended one out with the non suspended one.&nbsp; Obviously the normal "no aggro" rule would still apply.</P>
<P>Also heard that the dev team is looking at making invis not "poof" pets, which would be nice considering the no suspend/zoning thing.</P>
<P>- Bril</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
																		
