<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Vannja_Mahn wrote:<BR>
<DIV>What is the difference between running around a single zone with 2 fully buffed pets and crossing a zoneline with 2 fully buffed pets? The difference is a bonechip (and peridot), and some mana. You can still only have 1 pet active at a time.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Egad! you walked over the desert&nbsp;hill from North Ro to Oasis, your pets should poof now. Why does this make sense? </DIV>
<P><BR>
<HR>
</P>
<P>That was my point exactly.&nbsp; We can have 2 pets up anyway.&nbsp; If they are going to let pets zone, let em zone.&nbsp; Why arbitrarily say "You can have two pets if you take 2 mins out of your time to set them up, but only one of those can zone because it is too powerful to have two pets."&nbsp; </P>
<P>It just doesn't make any sense.</P>
<DIV>"Actually I believe buffs upon a suspended pet are halted.&nbsp; So that maybe part of their problem...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>- Bril"</DIV>
<P>Reread what he is saying.&nbsp; He is saying that in the same zone he can have two pets both fully buffed.&nbsp; Why can only one of those zone? He is 100% correct.&nbsp; The ONLY thing it costs is a bone chip, peridot, and mana.&nbsp; As our pets are the most costly to pop everytime we zone it is no wonder the Necro community is the biggest voice on this.&nbsp; </P>
<P>If what you are saying is .... They don't want us to use Suspended Minion cause buffs stop timing out that makes ZERO sense at all.&nbsp; I can simply run around with my pet Suspended and just pop it to zone and resuspend it on the other side and the buffs still last just as long&nbsp;(which is what I do most the time now anyway, because of prenerf Circlet of Shadows uberness).&nbsp;But that is a royal pain in the arse.&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
